Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.52,0:00:03.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(400,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.31,0:00:24.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sometime ago, for the sake of living, we left behind our happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.23,0:00:31.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We deceived ourselves, clinging to this mere illusion as we danced...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.53,0:00:37.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With closed eyes, at the end of the horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.79,0:00:43.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was searching for your smiling face...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.25,0:00:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We embrace our dreams and continue on...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.26,0:00:57.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}within the swaying traces of memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.19,0:01:04.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Someday, I will once again grasp hold of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.28,0:01:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}these feelings I have locked away in my heart... Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.90,0:01:32.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Haga! Ryuzaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.36,0:01:36.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are you guys saying that your despair is caused by Yugi and myself?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.82,0:01:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is it because of those vengeful thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.32,0:01:40.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}that you both decided to join forces with Doma and bet your souls?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.58,0:01:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm sorry, but we can't afford to lose to you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.00,0:01:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not before we wipe the floor with Doma, anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.54,0:01:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I'm worried about Yugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.46,0:01:51.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's still in shock from that defeat...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.09,0:01:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Can he Duel properly?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.96,0:01:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Timaeus Can't Be Activated"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.11,0:02:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.40,0:02:12.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.98,0:02:14.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse Trap open!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.98,0:02:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Activate Natural Selection!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.36,0:02:18.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.36,0:02:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Trap Card can only be activated during the opponent's turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.20,0:02:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can create a Monster identical to a chosen Monster on my opponent's field.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.50,0:02:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The original Monster is then destroyed by this card!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.37,0:02:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.58,0:02:32.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Monster I choose is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.92,0:02:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Insect Queen!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.43,0:02:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you've done it! How dare you destroy my queen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.68,0:02:49.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch carefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.06,0:02:50.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I offer this Insect Token as a sacrifice!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.02,0:02:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I Summon Soukou Hyakusoku - Armored Centipede!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.94,0:02:59.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take that!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.11,0:03:01.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use Armored Centipede to attack Kuriboh!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.04,0:03:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each Insect-Type Monster that Armor Centipede destroys...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.62,0:03:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...increases its Attack Points by 500!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.42,0:03:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.76,0:03:25.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Monster that resulted from Natural Selection...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.80,0:03:28.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...is destroyed when the opponent's turn ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.81,0:03:34.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now the only thing still on the field is the infected Retrained Elf Swordsman...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.49,0:03:40.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.65,0:03:43.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tyrant Dragon, destroy Red-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.50,0:03:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red-Eyes...!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.29,0:03:57.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We ain't done wit' you {\i1}yet{\i0}, Red-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.92,0:04:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We ain't ready ta' let ya take a nap yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.71,0:04:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Activate Reverse Trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.84,0:04:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chain of the Underworld!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.81,0:04:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.76,0:04:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red-Eyes got brought back?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.81,0:04:15.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chain of the Underworld is activated when the opponent's Monster is destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.56,0:04:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Attack a' the destroyed Monster goes down 700 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.48,0:04:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's returned as a Special Summoned card.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.57,0:04:24.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you planning to do, Ryuzaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.70,0:04:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you want to Summon back the Monster you defeated?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.78,0:04:31.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ya get it, Jounouchi?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.33,0:04:36.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tyrant Dragon is a Monster that can attack twice in the Battle Phase.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.50,0:04:40.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in order to do that, there's gotta be Monsters on the opponent's field.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.67,0:04:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.01,0:04:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you purposely revived Red-Eyes just so that you can send it to the Graveyard again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.30,0:04:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.14,0:04:51.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red-Eyes betrayed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.18,0:04:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't forgive it so easily!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.39,0:04:55.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, hurry up an' draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.52,0:04:57.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.02,0:05:02.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Chain of the Underworld is activated, the opponent gets ta' draw one card.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.28,0:05:03.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw one quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.40,0:05:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryuzaki, do you want to this badly...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.11,0:05:12.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that... supposed to be the punishment you have for Red-Eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.37,0:05:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything is caused by {\i1}you{\i0}, Jounouchi! All your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.12,0:05:20.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tyrant Dragon! Destroy Red-Eyes again!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.09,0:05:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you get your way!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.05,0:05:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse Trap, activate!\N Blessings of Birth!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.84,0:05:28.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You numb?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.93,0:05:31.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Traps ain't workin' 'gainst Tyrant Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.43,0:05:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who says I'm setting that trap for Tyrant Dragon?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.44,0:05:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When a Monster has been Special Summoned as per a special effect,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.36,0:05:49.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this card can end the opponent's turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.74,0:05:52.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryuzaki, your Battle Phase is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.95,0:05:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What'd ya say....?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.20,0:05:56.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red-Eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.62,0:05:59.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you enter the Graveyard again!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.26,0:06:09.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.68,0:06:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's finally time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.35,0:06:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The third turn of Parasite Caterpillar's Effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.44,0:06:22.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Retrained Elf Swordsman will be destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.19,0:06:24.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Poison Butterfly will be born!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.50,0:06:39.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.96,0:06:42.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You only got 300 Life Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.79,0:06:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much ya try, you'll never win!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.01,0:06:49.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be sure about that until the Duel is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.80,0:06:51.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.93,0:06:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.93,0:06:56.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Iron Knight Gearfried!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.94,0:07:03.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, I activate Magic Card, Pot of Greed!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.65,0:07:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This allows me to draw another two cards from my deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.70,0:07:13.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know, Ryuzaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.24,0:07:20.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Long ago, there was a Sword Master in the Duel Monsters World...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.58,0:07:24.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that was known to be "unbeatable" because he was too strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.80,0:07:31.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just one swing from the Sword Master's sword...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.84,0:07:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...can split the sea, tear the skies, and destroy the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.35,0:07:41.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was said that nobody ever returned alive after meeting him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.48,0:07:48.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because his power was too strong...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.19,0:07:52.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the Sword Master chained himself down and sealed his sword forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.66,0:07:54.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This seal will now be broken!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.66,0:07:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Magic Card, Release Restraint!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.37,0:08:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unchain yourself and descend!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.62,0:08:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sword Master - Naked Gear Freed!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.38,0:08:12.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.47,0:08:15.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His Attack Power is only 2600!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.01,0:08:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fancy creatin' such a scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.77,0:08:24.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've drawn The Claw of Hermos, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.27,0:08:26.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.98,0:08:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as Poison Butterfly exists on your field...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.69,0:08:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you'll suffer 500 points of damage every turn, starting right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.12,0:08:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Wh-What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.87,0:08:47.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me he has gotten that card?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.38,0:08:51.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed he did... Darn!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.59,0:08:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think that he drew that card at such a crucial point!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.51,0:08:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is as far as you can go, Haga!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.18,0:08:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll end this Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.85,0:09:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Monocle of Timaeus!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.56,0:09:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll fuse him together with Poison Butterfly to form...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.95,0:09:17.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Timaeus!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.03,0:09:19.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why...? Why won't it activate...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.04,0:09:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey now, don't go scaring people, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.08,0:09:29.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Did Timaeus abandon... me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.79,0:09:31.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.96,0:09:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You actually got abandoned by the card! How pathetic!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.01,0:09:38.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I were you, I wouldn't be able to take it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.97,0:09:43.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so embarrassing that I wouldn't even dare call myself a Duelist!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.14,0:09:46.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut you trap, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.23,0:09:47.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,End...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.69,0:09:50.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.23,0:09:52.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said "end"  just now, didn't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.61,0:09:56.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the Effect of Poison Butterfly will start right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.36,0:09:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Life Points will go down by 500!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.12,0:10:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yugi has only 700 Life Points now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.54,0:10:07.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If this goes on, the soul of the other Yugi will...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.08,0:10:10.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, you're finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.13,0:10:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.34,0:10:17.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one reverse card and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.35,0:10:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Claw of Hermos...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.02,0:10:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I remember that this card can be combined with any Monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.56,0:10:31.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...becomin' an Equipment Card.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.69,0:10:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be prepared, Ryuzaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.82,0:10:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate The Claw of Hermos!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.78,0:10:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sword Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.49,0:10:41.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna give you an ultimate sword!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.87,0:10:54.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I equip the Red-Eyes Black Dragon Sword to Naked Gear Freed!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.55,0:10:58.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this way, the Attack Power of the equipped Monster goes up by 1000 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.55,0:11:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, for every Dragon-Type Monster existing on the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.26,0:11:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,its Attack Power goes up by 500 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.30,0:11:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.56,0:11:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Tyrant Dragon is the only Dragon-Type Monster on the field currently...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.35,0:11:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So in total, the Attack increases by 1500 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.02,0:11:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naked Gear Freed now has an Attack Power of 4100 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.57,0:11:17.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.61,0:11:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Tyrant Dragon's gonna lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.86,0:11:24.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, when Naked Gear Freed is equipped with an Equipment Card...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.37,0:11:28.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has the Special Ability of destroying a Monster on the opponent's field, which activates now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.58,0:11:32.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, Tyrant Dragon is destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.13,0:11:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.04,0:11:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Tyrant Dragon is gone due to a Special Ability instead of a battle...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.26,0:11:44.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ryuzaki... You did have your soul taken away before, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.76,0:11:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But you went back to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.22,0:11:51.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So, there must surely be a way to save you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.77,0:11:56.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.73,0:11:58.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is why...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.07,0:12:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to {\i1}defeat{\i0} you in order to {\i1}save{\i0} you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.36,0:12:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here goes! Naked Gear Freed's attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.45,0:12:06.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Direct Attack on Ryuzaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.33,0:12:10.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dark Mega Slash!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.38,0:12:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Save me...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.03,0:12:43.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm sorry, Ryuzaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.66,0:12:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryuzaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.66,0:12:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get a grip, Ryuzaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.21,0:12:59.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is his soul really taken away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.09,0:13:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll definitely bring Ryuzaki's soul back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.72,0:13:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What Doma did was unforgivable!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.18,0:13:07.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Playing around with these people's hearts!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.76,0:13:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.76,0:13:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pegasus and Yugi as well... I'll bring everyone back to normal!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.85,0:13:15.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Mai, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.73,0:13:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just you wait, Doma!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.40,0:13:20.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never forgive you guys!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.73,0:13:24.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll defeat all of you!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.95,0:13:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.74,0:13:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.87,0:13:30.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're obviously gonna lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.41,0:13:32.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're really a king who doesn't know when to give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.75,0:13:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never give up until I save my partner with my own hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.96,0:13:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Magic Warrior Breaker!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.63,0:13:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This very moment, I activate a Trap Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.88,0:13:47.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Insect Swarm!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.39,0:13:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card has the effect of reducing the Attack of all Monsters on the field by 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.69,0:14:03.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, for each Monster a player controls, they receive 100 points damage per Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.16,0:14:09.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my victory, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.45,0:14:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You only have 500 of your Life Points left.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.58,0:14:16.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When this turn ends, Poison Butterfly's Effect will bring you to 0!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.96,0:14:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it'll be "the end" for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.25,0:14:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.09,0:14:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anzu-{\i1}chan{\i0}, you just sit there and watch him get defeated!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.59,0:14:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Yugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.10,0:14:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I recall some sort of {\i1}promise{\i0} before we began...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.39,0:14:36.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't I say that I'd tell you where your partner is if you beat me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.10,0:14:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I won't be able to tell you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.56,0:14:43.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you're going to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.82,0:14:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You scum!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.82,0:14:50.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But well, I have a very {\i1}kind{\i0} personality...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.16,0:14:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I'll do you a favor and tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.32,0:14:53.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you look so {\i1}pitiful{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.24,0:14:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw it... Your partner
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.91,0:15:03.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw the card that sealed the soul of the other Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.71,0:15:08.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is it?! Tell me!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.13,0:15:12.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get anxious, now! Calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.52,0:15:19.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is that card.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.94,0:15:20.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.89,0:15:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hand it over!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.44,0:15:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should I {\i1}do{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.52,0:15:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Since I pity you, I'll hand it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.03,0:15:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On second thought, forget it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.07,0:15:32.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How the hell {\i1}could{\i0} I?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.70,0:15:34.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in the midst of a {\i1}Duel{\i0} here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.70,0:15:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So let's get {\i1}on{\i0} with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.96,0:15:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-How could you...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.84,0:15:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haga!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.67,0:15:52.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kidding~! I was just pulling your leg~!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.80,0:15:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was just a normal card.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.80,0:15:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the worst!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.89,0:16:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was just a joke, a {\i1}joke{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.23,0:16:03.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare yourself, you stingy bug bastard!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.11,0:16:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Special Ability of Magical Warrior Breaker!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.16,0:16:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mana Break!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.16,0:16:25.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The... The Special Ability of Magical Warrior Breaker...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.54,0:16:27.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You {\i1}can't{\i0}...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.63,0:16:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When one Magic Counter is removed from Magical Warrior Breaker,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.30,0:16:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can destroy one Magic or Trap Card on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.39,0:16:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Destroy Insecticide Barrier, Magical Warrior Breaker!!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.15,0:16:52.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Effect can only be used once with every Magic Counter expended.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.61,0:16:56.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once this Effect is activated, the Magic Counter disappears....
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.57,0:17:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the Attack Power of Breaker goes down by 300 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.37,0:17:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I can attack with the Poison Butterfly you gave me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.71,0:17:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,NOOOO~!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.92,0:17:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here goes, insect asshole!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.88,0:17:12.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use Poison Butterfly to attack Armored Centipede!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.97,0:17:21.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not over yet!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.27,0:17:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use Magical Warrior Breaker to Direct Attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.65,0:17:32.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.07,0:17:35.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now, you have no more Monsters to attack with!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.61,0:17:38.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And because of Poison Butterfly's Effect, your Life Points will become zero!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.24,0:17:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.49,0:17:43.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I win!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.04,0:17:45.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you {\i1}mistaken{\i0} about something?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.29,0:17:49.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Battle Phase is not over!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.71,0:17:51.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.09,0:17:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't all your Monsters finished their attacks?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.01,0:17:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate a Quick-Play Magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.43,0:17:59.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Berserker Soul!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.01,0:18:01.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Berserker Soul?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.81,0:18:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can activate this when I discard all cards I have on hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.81,0:18:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can keep drawing cards until I reach a non-Monster Card.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.15,0:18:13.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I have to discard them into the Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.57,0:18:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, for each monster card that I've discarded...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.40,0:18:19.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Monster with 1500 or less Attack Power allows me to keep attacking!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.57,0:18:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Monster with 1500 or less Attack Points?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.04,0:18:26.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.50,0:18:35.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Once this Effect is activated, the Magic Counter disappears....
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.51,0:18:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And the Attack Power of Breaker goes down by 300 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.55,0:18:42.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.05,0:18:43.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He planned this far ahead...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.89,0:18:45.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I come!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.27,0:18:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first card, draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.39,0:18:51.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I discard the Monster Card, Queen's Knight into the Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.98,0:18:56.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magical Warrior Breaker, additional attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.91,0:19:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I draw the second card!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.95,0:19:05.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monster Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.88,0:19:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The third card!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.71,0:19:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monster Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.84,0:19:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.26,0:19:19.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monster Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.18,0:19:22.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.09,0:19:23.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monster Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.35,0:19:26.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.35,0:19:27.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monster Card!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.06,0:19:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.98,0:19:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monster Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.11,0:19:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.19,0:19:40.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monster Car-
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.07,0:19:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it already, Yugi!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.74,0:19:44.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let go of me!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.78,0:19:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haga's Life Points dropped to 0 a long time ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.20,0:19:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's clearly your victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.89,0:20:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.35,0:20:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After Dueling with the ones chosen by the Legendary Dragons,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.32,0:20:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,their souls have become much more powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.36,0:20:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You became valuable sacrifices for our God to revive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.04,0:20:32.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haga, I won!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.29,0:20:33.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You promised me! So tell me!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.75,0:20:35.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is my Partner?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.63,0:20:41.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Out with it! You promised me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.55,0:20:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is my Partner? Where is he?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.13,0:20:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.09,0:20:46.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.26,0:20:48.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know that too, Yugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.72,0:20:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haga's soul has already taken away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.73,0:20:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,HAGA!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.94,0:20:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why Haga made a promise like that... He couldn't have kept it from the start!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.94,0:20:59.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speak!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.90,0:21:03.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Partner...!! WHERE {\i1}IS{\i0} HE!!?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.53,0:21:05.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Poor Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.28,0:21:08.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Partner...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.41,0:21:14.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.67,0:21:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.93,0:21:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.18,0:22:02.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The houses lined down the street drifting by being dyed red
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.54,0:22:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I notice pain, it'll turn into happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.15,0:22:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Every time people wipe away tears, they understand bonds
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.22,0:22:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The warm strength that you gave me will change into kindness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.70,0:22:40.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Overflowing feelings don't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.98,0:22:50.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll live while I feel it, for me to be myself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.88,0:22:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Healed by overflowing friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.03,0:23:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our fated encounter is a truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.55,0:23:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and someday we'll be able to understand each other
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.21,0:23:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, who was still trapped by the darkness in his heart, managed to beat Haga.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.79,0:23:26.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the train got derailed and fell into the valley.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.51,0:23:29.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're still alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.51,0:23:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When we regained conscious...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.30,0:23:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We found that we were saved by an old man who guards the valley and a young girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.47,0:23:38.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are they exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.10,0:23:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do they know about Yugi?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.06,0:23:43.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, "Battle! The Two Yugis"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.86,0:23:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
